ink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lsu1665703133058.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lsu1665703133058.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lsu1665703133058.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lsu1665703133058\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__uwritestringsyssetting_411866\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copies a string to a specified section of a specified <span class=\"ph filepath\">ini</span>\n      file.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__topic_d124796e1_d124797e1_d124798e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104lsu1665703133058_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__codeblock_hkg_t4l_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int uwritestringsyssetting (char*section, char*key, char*value, char*iniFile);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__topic_d87972e1_d87973e1_d87974e1_d87975e1_d87976e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d654278e64\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__parml_m3k_v4l_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">section</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Name of the section to which the string will be copied. If the section does not\n                  exist, it will be created.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">key</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Name of the key to be associated with the string. If the key does not exist in\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">section</var>, it will be created. If <var class=\"keyword varname\">key</var> is\n                  NULL, the entire section is deleted, including all keys within the section.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">value</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">String to be written to the file. If NULL, the key pointed to by the\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">key</var> parameter is deleted.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">iniFile</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Name of the initialization file</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__topic_d87977e1_d87978e1_d87979e1_d87980e1_d87981e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d654278e122\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by uwritestringsyssetting</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__1\">&lt;&gt;0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__2\">Success. The string was copied to the\n                        initialization file.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lsu1665703133058__table_d15011e1_d15012e1_d15013e1__entry__2\">The function failed. To get extended error\n                        information, call the Windows function\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetLastError</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__topic_d87982e1_d87983e1_d87984e1_d87985e1_d87986e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d654278e177\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__d6584e20\">Microsoft Windows platforms only. Library:\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">ulib</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__topic_d87987e1_d87988e1_d87989e1_d87990e1_d87991e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d654278e190\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__p_d124829e1_d124830e1_d124831e1\">This function is a wrapper for the Windows API\n            function <code class=\"ph codeph\">WritePrivateProfileString</code> and follows the same rules. For\n            extensive information about this function, visit the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"http://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/docs/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Microsoft DN technical documentation site</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104lsu1665703133058_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"lsu1665703133058__codeblock_n1l_fpl_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\nuwritestringsyssetting(\"mysection\",\"mykey,\"myvalue\",ugetprofile());</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zft1665703132860.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetprofile</a><p>Return a pointer to the name of the current .ini file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eux1665703132929.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ureadstringsyssetting</a><p>Read a string from the specified section of a specified ini file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xnc1665702891206.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Calling Windows GetLastError() Function</a><p>In a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name ULASTERROR rather than calling GetLastError().</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uwritestringsyssetting Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copies a string to a specified section of a specified ini file. Explain this code int uwritestringsyssetting (char*section, char*key, char*value, char*iniFile); Copy Parameters section Name of the section to which the string will be copied. If the section does not exist, it will be created. key Name of the key to be associated with the string. If the key does not exist in section , it will be created. If key is NULL, the entire section is deleted, including all keys within the section. value String to be written to the file. If NULL, the key pointed to by the key parameter is deleted. iniFile Name of the initialization file Return Values Table 1. Values returned by uwritestringsyssetting Value Meaning <>0 Success. The string was copied to the initialization file. 0 The function failed. To get extended error information, call the Windows function GetLastError . Use Microsoft Windows platforms only. Library: ulib Description This function is a wrapper for the Windows API function WritePrivateProfileString and follows the same rules. For extensive information about this function, visit the Microsoft DN technical documentation site . Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> uwritestringsyssetting(\"mysection\",\"mykey,\"myvalue\",ugetprofile()); Copy Related Links ugetprofile Return a pointer to the name of the current .ini file. ureadstringsyssetting Read a string from the specified section of a specified ini file. Calling Windows GetLastError() Function In a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name ULASTERROR rather than calling GetLastError(). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}